  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="AN154.1-kilavi">viṉaimuṟṟiya talaimakaṉ <app><lem>pākaṟkuc</lem><rdg wit="#C2 #C3 #C7 #C9 #RK">ṟēr pākaṟkuc</rdg></app> colliyatu.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en">What he who had finished [his] work said to the charioteer.</p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
            <lg xml:id="AN154.1">
              <l>paṭumaḻai poḻinta payamiku puṟavi</l>
              <l>ṉeṭunī ravala pakuvāyt tērai</l>
              <l>ciṟupal liyatti ṉeṭuneṟik kaṟaṅkak</l>
              <l>kuṟumpukaṭ piṭavi ṉeṭuṅkā lalari</l>
              <l>cennila maruṅki <supplied>ṉu</supplied>ṇṇayir varippa</l>
              <l>veñciṉa varaviṉ paiyaṇart taṉṉa</l>
              <l>taṇkamaḻ kōṭa <supplied>ṟā</supplied>tupiṇi yaviḻat</l>
              <l>tirimarup piralait teḷḷaṟal parukik</l>
              <l>kāmar piṇaiyō ṭēmuṟa vatiyak</l>
              <l>kāṭukaviṉ peṟṟa taṇpatap peruvaḻi</l>
              <l>yōṭupari meliyāk koycuvaṟ puravit</l>
              <l>tōṭār tārmaṇi taya<supplied>ṅ</supplied>ku <supplied>pi</supplied>yampa</l>
              <l>vūrmati valava tērē cīrmikupu</l>
              <l><supplied>nam</supplied>vayiṟ purinta koḷkai</l>
              <l>yammā varivaiyait tuṉṉukam viraintē.</l>
            </lg>
            <lg xml:lang="en">
                <l>In the woodlands abounding in yield, inundated by falling rain (1)</l>
                <l>as split-mouthed frogs in a hollow of stagnant water (2)</l>
                <l>resound on the long paths like many small instruments, (3)</l>
                <l>when the long-stalked blossoms of the Piṭavu by the stronghold (4)</l>
                <l>make patterns in the fine sand by the side of the red soil, (5)</l>
                <l>while the pollen opens [its] bonds on the cool fragrant white Malabar lily, (7)</l>
                <l>like the rising hood of a snake in hot fury, (6)</l>
                <l>when the Iralai with twisted horns dwells joyfully</l>
                <l>with [its] desired mate, drinking clear water, (8f.)</l>
                <l>on the wide road, at the moment of coolness when the forest has obtained [its] beauty, (10)</l>
                <l>so that the bells will shake [and] sound, in a garland that rings in a cluster (12)</l>
                <l>on the horses with trimmed manes that don’t soften [their] running gait (11)</l>
                <l>mount, charioteer, the chariot. (13a-c)</l>
                <l>With [our] prosperity increased, [true to] the vows cherished on our part (13d-14)</l>
                <l>we shall hurriedly approach [our] pretty dark woman. (15)</l>
            </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
  </text>
